# EJS Views and Bootstrap Rules

## Scope
- Server-rendered views live in `apps/api/views/**/*.ejs`.
- Shared partials are in `apps/api/views/parts/*.ejs`.

## Layout Parts
Include shared parts in this order:
1. `head.ejs` -> `head-end.ejs`
2. `body.ejs` (includes navigation)
3. Page content inside `<main>`
4. `body-end.ejs`

## Partials Contract
- `navigation.ejs`: main + mobile nav, reads `url`, `isLoggedIn`, `userName`; includes `success-notification.ejs`.
- `success-notification.ejs`: renders first success flash message from `success[0]`.
- `error-msg.ejs`: handles string or array `errorMessage` values.
- `add-to-cart.ejs`: reusable POST form to `/cart` with hidden `id` and `_csrf`.

## Form Rules
- Every POST form must include:
  - `<input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>">`
- Reuse `apps/api/views/parts/add-to-cart.ejs` for add-to-cart UI.
- Default to standard form posts; avoid introducing fetch/AJAX unless requested.

## Locals Expected by Views
Set globally in `apps/api/app.ts`:
- `isLoggedIn`
- `userName`
- `csrfToken`
- `error`
- `success`

Set per-render in controllers:
- `pageTitle`
- `url`
- `errorMessage` when a view-specific error state is needed

## Styling Rules
- Keep Bootstrap-compatible markup.
- Keep project custom styles in `apps/api/public/css/*.css`.
- Avoid inline `<style>` blocks.

## Do Not
- Do not remove `_csrf` hidden field from POST forms.
- Do not duplicate shared partial logic inline across many pages.
- Do not introduce frontend frameworks inside EJS templates.
